"With over 70 years of experience, a real estate network of more than 85 million square feet across 1,400 facilities, in over 50 countries, Iron Mountain is the global leader for records and information management. Our services help businesses of all sizes and industries lower cost and risk, comply with regulations, recover from disaster and enable a more digital way of working. With a driving passion to protect, Iron Mountain vows to treat the information and assets of our customers as if they were our own. Visit our website for more information.   SECURE SHREDDING SERVICES - Choose between our onsite and offsite shredding services. Have one of our mobile shred trucks come to you for witnessed shredding, or opt for one of our uniformed drivers to pick up and securely transport your documents to a nearby Iron Mountain shred plant. Our shredding service is designed so that you can get the help you need, when you need it. Request a service, see how much material you've shredded or how many trees you've saved at any time of day through our online portal. Confused on what to keep and what to destroy? Our 24/7/365 customer support team is here to answer all of your questions. Most importantly, your shredding program is fully customizable to fit your organizations unique needs. Choose from witnessed onsite shredding or offsite shredding, multiple bin sizes, online scheduling and pre-arranged pickups, and enjoy the freedom to change your program at any time.   RECORDS MANAGEMENT & DOCUMENT STORAGE - Securely store your important records and business items close to home. Say goodbye to the hassles of packing and hauling boxes to a storage unit or trying to find a box in a packed basement. Our records management and document storage services are designed so that you can get the help you need, when you need it. Your records are accessible online with just a few simple clicks, and our 24/7/365 customer support team is here to answer all of your questions. Even better, our records management and document storage services are fully customizable- whether you're looking to store just a few boxes or an entire warehouse, we have an affordable package built to meet your needs and grow alongside your business.  DOCUMENT SCANNING SERVICES - Our expertly trained scanning specialists follow proven practices to ensure that we meet your requirements without sacrificing quality. Once scanned, images are securely delivered in the format you select. Our scanning solutions offer instant access through Iron Mountain Digital Record Center, your central electronic repository for the documents that we have imaged from your paper records. Search for, retrieve and share the information you need from any location, on any device, at any time of day. Whether youre looking to scan just a few critical documents or an entire office, we have an affordable package to meet and grow with your business needs.    IT ASSET DESTRUCTION SERVICES - Our secure ITAD solution prioritizes your business data security, sustainability and brand reputation. Well help you destroy, recycle and/or remarket your retired IT equipment through a reliable, environmentally-friendly and compliant process. Our ITAD approach will help you reduce e-waste and retain maximum value from your end-of-life IT assets, including your computers, mobile phones, servers, hard drives and more. We offer secure logistics and a rigorous chain-of-custody so that you can rest assured your data and reputation remains safe through technology transitions."

general_info: The story of the Ray Laks Family of Dealerships starts in 1963, when Ray Laks opened his first dealership on Delaware Avenue in Buffalo and began a tradition of selling great cars and trucks that continues to this day.  In 1968  the store was moved to 120 Orchard Park Rd in West Seneca.  Picking up Honda in 1971, Ray Laks Honda quickly became WNY's #1 selling Honda Dealership and is WNY's oldest Honda dealer.  Already known for providing great service, the expansion continued, and a body shop was opened in 1972 to provide for more his customers needs.  Ray Laks was getting more involved with the community as well, beginning work with hospice of Buffalo and other local charities.  The addition of Acura in 1995, one of the original 50 Acura dealerships in the United States, and expansion of the dealerships' presence in the Pre-Owned market allowed for more buying power and savings that could be passed down to the consumer. Acquiring Mitsubishi in 2006, Ray Laks added to its growing, loyal customer base.  Employing over 200 of your friends and neighbors in Western New York and selling nearly 2,500 cars every year, the Ray Laks Family of Dealerships looks forward to serving you, our customers, old friends and new, for many years to come.

general_info: "With over 70 years of experience, a real estate network of more than 85 million square feet across 1,400 facilities, in over 50 countries, Iron Mountain is the global leader for records and information management. Over 75,000 small businesses across the world rely on us to protect information, unlock insights and transform operations through our range of services, including: document scanning and shredding, secure IT asset disposition, physical and digital/cloud storage, and more. Our services help businesses of all sizes and industries lower cost and risk, comply with regulations, recover from disaster and enable a more digital way of working. With a driving passion to protect, Iron Mountain vows to treat the information and assets of our customers as if they were our own. Visit our website for more information.   SECURE SHREDDING SERVICES - Choose between our onsite and offsite shredding services. Have one of our mobile shred trucks come to you for witnessed shredding, or opt for one of our uniformed drivers to pick up and securely transport your documents to a nearby Iron Mountain shred plant. Our shredding service is designed so that you can get the help you need, when you need it. Request a service, see how much material you've shredded or how many trees you've saved at any time of day through our online portal. Confused on what to keep and what to destroy? Our 24/7/365 customer support team is here to answer all of your questions. Most importantly, your shredding program is fully customizable to fit your organizations unique needs. Choose from witnessed onsite shredding or offsite shredding, multiple bin sizes, online scheduling and pre-arranged pickups, and enjoy the freedom to change your program at any time.   RECORDS MANAGEMENT & DOCUMENT STORAGE - Securely store your important records and business items close to home. Say goodbye to the hassles of packing and hauling boxes to a storage unit or trying to find a box in a packed basement. Our records management and document storage services are designed so that you can get the help you need, when you need it. Your records are accessible online with just a few simple clicks, and our 24/7/365 customer support team is here to answer all of your questions. Even better, our records management and document storage services are fully customizable- whether you're looking to store just a few boxes or an entire warehouse, we have an affordable package built to meet your needs and grow alongside your business.  DOCUMENT SCANNING SERVICES - Our expertly trained scanning specialists follow proven practices to ensure that we meet your requirements without sacrificing quality. Once scanned, images are securely delivered in the format you select. Our scanning solutions offer instant access through Iron Mountain Digital Record Center, your central electronic repository for the documents that we have imaged from your paper records. Search for, retrieve and share the information you need from any location, on any device, at any time of day. Whether youre looking to scan just a few critical documents or an entire office, we have an affordable package to meet and grow with your business needs.    IT ASSET DESTRUCTION SERVICES - Our secure ITAD solution prioritizes your business data security, sustainability and brand reputation. Well help you destroy, recycle and/or remarket your retired IT equipment through a reliable, environmentally-friendly and compliant process. Our ITAD approach will help you reduce e-waste and retain maximum value from your end-of-life IT assets, including your computers, mobile phones, servers, hard drives and more. We offer secure logistics and a rigorous chain-of-custody so that you can rest assured your data and reputation remains safe through technology transitions."

general_info: "With over 70 years of experience, a real estate network of more than 85 million square feet across 1,400 facilities, in over 50 countries, Iron Mountain is the global leader for records and information management. Over 75,000 small businesses across the world rely on us to protect information, unlock insights and transform operations through our range of services, including: document scanning and shredding, secure IT asset disposition, physical and digital/cloud storage, and more. Our services help businesses of all sizes and industries lower cost and risk, comply with regulations, recover from disaster and enable a more digital way of working. With a driving passion to protect, Iron Mountain vows to treat the information and assets of our customers as if they were our own. Visit our website for more information.   SECURE SHREDDING SERVICES - Choose between our onsite and offsite shredding services. Have one of our mobile shred trucks come to you for witnessed shredding, or opt for one of our uniformed drivers to pick up and securely transport your documents to a nearby Iron Mountain shred plant. Our shredding service is designed so that you can get the help you need, when you need it. Request a service, see how much material you've shredded or how many trees you've saved at any time of day through our online portal. Confused on what to keep and what to destroy? Our 24/7/365 customer support team is here to answer all of your questions. Most importantly, your shredding program is fully customizable to fit your organizations unique needs. Choose from witnessed onsite shredding or offsite shredding, multiple bin sizes, online scheduling and pre-arranged pickups, and enjoy the freedom to change your program at any time.   RECORDS MANAGEMENT & DOCUMENT STORAGE - Securely store your important records and business items close to home. Say goodbye to the hassles of packing and hauling boxes to a storage unit or trying to find a box in a packed basement. Our records management and document storage services are designed so that you can get the help you need, when you need it. Your records are accessible online with just a few simple clicks, and our 24/7/365 customer support team is here to answer all of your questions. Even better, our records management and document storage services are fully customizable- whether you're looking to store just a few boxes or an entire warehouse, we have an affordable package built to meet your needs and grow alongside your business.  DOCUMENT SCANNING SERVICES - Our expertly trained scanning specialists follow proven practices to ensure that we meet your requirements without sacrificing quality. Once scanned, images are securely delivered in the format you select. Our scanning solutions offer instant access through Iron Mountain Digital Record Center, your central electronic repository for the documents that we have imaged from your paper records. Search for, retrieve and share the information you need from any location, on any device, at any time of day. Whether youre looking to scan just a few critical documents or an entire office, we have an affordable package to meet and grow with your business needs.    IT ASSET DESTRUCTION SERVICES - Our secure ITAD solution prioritizes your business data security, sustainability and brand reputation. Well help you destroy, recycle and/or remarket your retired IT equipment through a reliable, environmentally-friendly and compliant process. Our ITAD approach will help you reduce e-waste and retain maximum value from your end-of-life IT assets, including your computers, mobile phones, servers, hard drives and more. We offer secure logistics and a rigorous chain-of-custody so that you can rest assured your data and reputation remains safe through technology transitions."

Are you looking for affordable, clean, safe, and secure storage in Sacramento? At StoragePRO, our first priority is YOU! We now offer 100% no-contact online rentals. What does this mean for you? 
 
You do not need to come into the office to rent or access your storage unit. Renting and all document signing is completed online. StoragePRO is also committed to providing a clean, safe, and secure storage experience when you are on site. 
 
StoragePRO is following the most rigorous cleaning and safety practices and each store is disinfected bi-weekly, with state-of-the-art electrostatic cleaners. 
 
Whether you are storing items for your business, a few personal items, or your entire household, we have the perfect storage space to fit your needs. From our economy 5x5 units to our premium 10x30 units and our RV, boat, and vehicle storage, our on-site managers will provide expert guidance and excellent customer service to help you find the perfect storage space.

Security is our top priority. Our store is well-lit, fenced and gated, and has 24-hour video surveillance. Our on-site manager provides extra security.  
 
For your boat, RV or automobile, we have wide driveways and wide parking spaces.  
 
In need of moving supplies?  Unit locks, bubble wrap, packing tape and boxes in various sizes are available on-site at affordable prices.  
 
Give us a call or come on over and take a look at our conveniently located Sacramento storage units. We will be happy to help you choose the right one for you.  
 
Ask about our move-in specials!

There's a framed sign at the Code Shred offices that reads:   
 
 
The secret to document shredding success? 
 
 
D.W.Y.S.Y.W.D.! 
 
 
It's a conversation piece for our document destruction clients, a surprising number of whom get it right away: Do What You Say You Will Do! 
 
 
Whether it's mobile shredding, paper shredding, document shredding, or any other document destruction service designed to help you comply with HIPAA, the Graham-Leach Bliley Act, or any other mandated privacy protection requirement, at Code Shred, we really do what we say we will do.  
 
 
Prompt, Dependable Shredding Service 
 
 
We always answer the phone. We come when we say we will be there. We pride ourselves on being on time. As one customer said, "I can't believe it! It's been three months, and you not only answer the phone you actually showed up each and every time you said you would. No other document shredding company I know does that!"  
It's a sad fact, but many companies in the document shredding, paper shredding, document destruction, and mobile shredding business really don't answer the phone or offer you the kind of shredding services you deserve. Many are one- or two-person shops that have lost sight of the fact that there are now many places you can turn to for your document destruction and document shredding needs.  
 
 
Straight Talk about Pricing 
 
 
These are the same companies that are coy about their pricing models. They won't give you a straight answer when you ask what it's going to cost.

general_info: Established in 1974, The Rockefeller Archive Center is an independent institution that provides reference services for researchers. It is a division of The Rockefeller University .The center serves more than 250 on-site researchers annually. It includes a collection of business records and documents on various topics. The Rockefeller Archive Center features more than 35,000 cubic feet of documents, over 500,000 photographs and nearly 3,000 films related to various subjects, such as agriculture, art, international relations and economic development. The center also maintains archival storage vaults and a reading room that accommodates more than five researchers. The Rockefeller Archive Center preserves documents of The Rockefeller University, Rockefeller Foundation and Rockefeller Brothers Fund. It additionally has a collection of documents from nonprofit organizations. The center is located in Sleepy Hollow, N.Y.

general_info: SSDiesel SupplyTM was formed in 2003 by Walt L. in Tonawanda, NY USA. Tonawanda being the home of one of GM's largest engine plant, Tonawanda Engine, ( home of the Big-Block Chevy ), Walt grew up a gearhead building countless hot rods, musclecars and custom motorcycles. Honing his skills through the years as an ASE Certified Master Diesel Technician, Industrial Service Technician, and eventually in management, including managing a truck dealership and Technical Service Manager in the Heat-Transfer Industry for a Fortune 100 Company. Walt's interest in diesels peaked back in the early 80's when he purchased a 5.7 diesel engine to custom install in a '72 Chevelle. From there he acquired a GM 6.2 diesel p/u, which he quickly modified with the installation of a Banks Turbo and other performance accessories, then purchasing several 6.5TD's. Realizing the high quality of the 6.5 TD engine, but discovering it's minor weaknesses, he came up with a solution to the chronic temperature related failures encountered with the PMD location. His design was based on his education and vast experience in both the mechanical and heat transfer industries. Walt's ingenious little device trademarked "FSD Heat-SyncTM" was born out of necessity. After extensive testing and the unit was proven to work, several units were sold to friends and acquaintances, and eventually word of mouth spread and demand for sales of his unit soared and spawned the idea of SSDiesel SupplyTM being formed. SSDiesel SupplyTM has undergone rapid growth and transformation in 2004 and set up their operation at 2307 Military Road in Tonawanda mid 2004. In just a year's time SSDiesel SupplyTM outgrew the Tonawanda facility, and moved their operations to a new 6000 sq ft facility located in in Kenmore NY, in June 2005. Now 3 years later, we've outgrown that and decided to buy our own much larger building. Effective August 1, 2008 our new address is 829 Sheridan Dr., NY 14150 Tonawanda This purchase represents a significant investment by Walt into the future of the company and in pleasing our customers. We're located a 1/2 mile east of Dunlop Tire, the only tire factory in the world making tires for Harley-Davidson, and 1/2 mile north of GM Powertrain Tonawanda, home of the Big Block Chevy! A true motorhead's dream!
